 MBOMBELA –   The suspects allegedly escaped when the vehicle came to a halt at the robots opposite the Nelspruit Fire Department.  According to Divergent Ops founder Jacques Meiring, their team arrested three of the suspect who were hiding in the bushes nearby Laerskool Nelspruit.  The other two suspects were caught by ACS armed response security members and SAPS. Witnesses at the scene stated they had heard shots fired during the incident. ALSO READ: Theft out of motor vehicles a persistent problem in Mbombela SAPS and security vehicles are busy patrolling various suburbs. A police helicopter could also be seen flying over the city in search of the remaining men. ALSO READ: Three field rangers arrested for poaching in KNP This is a developing story and Lowvelder will update as more information becomes available.